fields.physical_description:
Angled roof of maple and pine held together with glue, screws and bolts.
[Box] box lid, white card printed in colours to show photographs of various structures, the titles in three languages and maker's details
[Box] white card
[Roof] roof half of pale maple with red painted trim, glued together; pre assembled floor, back wall and 45° roof; large hole for access to room contents; various holes for screws, dowels and lock bolts
[Roof] as B.145:3-1998
[Roof part] roof batten of very pale maple wood with red painted trim; with tongues to fit into roof grooves
[Roof part] as B.145:5-1998
[Roof part] tongue for joing the roof halves; maple wood
[Lock] lock for double bolts, metal probably steel
[Lock] as B.145:8-1998
[Lock] as B.145:8-1998
[Lock] as B.145:8-1998
[Lock] as B.145:8-1998
[Lock] as B.145:8-1998
[Bolt] double bolt, metal probably steel
[Bolt] as B.145:14-1998
[Bolt] as B.145:14-1998
[Dowel] dowel, pine
[Dowel] as B.145:17-1998
[Key] key for the locks, metal probably steel
[Instructions] assembly instructions with text in three languages; showing black and white photographs and diagrams
[Catalogue] Bodo Hennig 1998 Catalogue, printed in colours to show photographs of various houses, furnitures and dolls, together with text.
